race.comment: KING OF MINTO (9) returned in fine fashion with a dominant victory here and looks the runner in this field with the most upside. Only needs some luck navigating from the sticky draw to be playing a major role in the outcome. LARIDAE (8) saves his best form for his home circuit here with three wins from just five spins. Has been given a bit of a freshen up and rates as a genuine top-three contender on best figures. Looks some value. The well-related WILD GYPSY (10) (half to G1 winner Wild Ruler) will strip fitter second-up from the spell and must be respected out of the Gollan yard. In the mix. I'M HEROIC (3) best of the rest while fresh.
